{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"body":"ROOT-CAUSE UPDATE (post-deploy diagnosis). The first dc33 fix (change #643, landed) provisions the tickets worktree + parses the rebar-ticket trailer, but the DEPLOYED store came up BROKEN: the boot 'git clone --single-branch --branch tickets' failed silently (masked by the entrypoint '|| echo clone deferred'), leaving an EMPTY repo (git rev-list --count HEAD = 0, HEAD broken). run_ensures then created .env-id on the empty repo, so it LOOKED converged but held zero tickets -> rebar.comment could not resolve any ticket ('not found'). A broken .git also defeats the '[ ! -d .git ]' re-clone guard, so it never self-heals. Separately, a clone-once store goes STALE: the auto-lander (unlike the review-bot, which only CREATES its own artifacts) must resolve tickets OTHER agents created after boot. Manual 'git fetch origin tickets' from the container SUCCEEDS (creds/network fine; dc33 events present on origin/tickets), confirming it's a boot-time clone failure, not an auth issue.\n\nFIX (follow-up change, branch fix-dc33-freshen): close_ticket_via_rebar now FRESHENS the store before annotating - fetch origin tickets + hard reset + run_ensures (re-clones if not a repo) - which self-heals the broken/empty clone AND keeps it current, in one place. Paging policy: unset REBAR_TRACKER_DIR pages (real misconfig, per the reporter's 'missing store is a real error'); a transient refresh failure is a non-paging skip (self-heals next landing); a rebar.comment failure on a FRESH store still pages. Entrypoint also re-fetches a 0-commit clone (defense in depth). Note: the auto-lander CORE (landing) is unaffected and proven (#642, #618 landed cleanly); this is the courtesy-annotation path only."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783974036072265001,"uuid":"f5d20c65-4cc6-404d-b7c4-a5741118b5a3"}